'''10-Hydroxydecanic acid''' is a specialized [[Saturated fat|saturated fatty acid]] that is a minor constituent of [[royal jelly]].<ref>{{Cite journal|title = Isolation and characterization of some hydroxy fatty and phosphoric acid esters of 10-hydroxy-2-decenoic acid from the royal jelly of honeybees (Apis mellifera)|url = https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11745-005-1445-6|journal = Lipids|date = 2005-08-01|issn = 0024-4201|pages = 833–838|volume = 40|issue = 8|doi = 10.1007/s11745-005-1445-6|language = en|first = Naoki|last = Noda|first2 = Kazue|last2 = Umebayashi|first3 = Takafumi|last3 = Nakatani|first4 = Kazumoto|last4 = Miyahara|first5 = Kaori|last5 = Ishiyama}}</ref> It was scientifically discovered in 1957.<ref>{{Cite journal|title = Über den Weiselzellenfuttersaft der Honigbiene I. Isolierung, Konstitutionsermittlung und Vorkommen der 10-Hydroxy-Δ 2 -decensäure|url = http://www.degruyter.com/view/j/bchm2.1957.308.issue-1/bchm2.1957.308.1.284/bchm2.1957.308.1.284.xml|journal = Hoppe-Seyler's Zeitschrift für physiologische Chemie|pages = 284–289|volume = 308|issue = Jahresband|doi = 10.1515/bchm2.1957.308.1.284|first = Adolf|last = Butenandt|first2 = Heinz|last2 = Rembold}}</ref>
