{{Speciesbox | name = Dwarf panchax | status = LC | status_system = iucn3.1 | image = | image_alt = | image_caption = | genus = Aplocheilus | species = parvus | authority = (Raj, 1916) }} '''''Aplocheilus parvus''''', the '''dwarf panchax''', is a [[species]] of [[Aplocheilidae|killifish]] [[Indigenous (ecology)|native]] to [[India]] and [[Sri Lanka]]. This species grows to a length of {{convert|6.3|cm|in|abbr=on}}. Its natural habitats are sheltered fresh and [[brackish water]] tanks, small streams and rivulets overgrown with vegetation. They are rarely use as an aquarium fish. It is often misidentified as ''[[Aplocheilus panchax]]'' or as ''[[Aplocheilus blockii]]''.<ref>{{FishBase species |genus= Aplocheilus|species= parvus| month = August | year = 2012}}</ref>
