{{Other uses|Granule (disambiguation)}}

A '''granule''' is a [[clastic rocks|clast]] of [[rock (geology)|rock]] with a [[particle size]] of 2 to 4 millimetres based on the [[Particle size (grain size)|Krumbein phi scale]] of [[sedimentology]]. Granules are generally considered to be larger than [[sand]] (0.0625 to 2 millimetres diameter) and smaller than [[pebble]]s (4 to 64 millimetres diameter). A rock made predominantly of granules is termed a granule [[Conglomerate (geology)|conglomerate]].<ref name="Folk1980a">Folk, R.L. (1980) ''The Petrology of Sedimentary Rocks.'' Austin, Texas, Hemphill Publishing Company. 182 pp. {{ISBN|0-914696-14-9}}</ref>

