{{Chembox | ImageFile = | ImageSize = | ImageAlt = | ImageName = | ImageFile_Ref = {{chemboximage|correct|??}} | IUPACName = Iron tetraboride | OtherNames = |Section1={{Chembox Identifiers | CASNo = | PubChem = | SMILES = }} |Section2={{Chembox Properties | Formula = FeB<sub>4</sub> | MolarMass = 99.0920 g/mol | Appearance = | Density = | MeltingPt = | BoilingPt = | Solubility = }} |Section3={{Chembox Hazards | MainHazards = | FlashPt = | AutoignitionPt = }} |Section4={{Chembox Structure | CrystalStruct = [[Orthorhombic crystal system|orthorhombic]] | Coordination = | MolShape = }} }}
'''Iron tetraboride''' (FeB<sub>4</sub>) is a [[superhard]] [[superconductor]] ([[Superconductivity#Superconducting phase transition|T<sub>c</sub>]] < 3[[Kelvin|K]]) consisting of [[iron]] and [[boron]]. Iron tetraboride does not occur in nature and can be created synthetically.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Discovery of a superhard iron tetraboride superconductor|last1=Gou|first1=Huiyang|date=18 April 2013 |arxiv=1304.5106 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.111.157002 |volume=111 |journal=Physical Review Letters|bibcode=2013PhRvL.111o7002G}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=http://physics.aps.org/featured-article-pdf/10.1103/PhysRevLett.111.157002 |date=11 October 2013 |title=Discovery of a Superhard Iron Tetraboride Superconductor |journal=Physical Review Letters |volume=111 |issue=157002 |pages=157002 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.111.157002 |accessdate=17 October 2013 |last1=Gou|first1=Huiyang |last2=Dubrovinskaia|first2=Natalia |last3=Bykova|first3=Elena |last4=Tsirlin|first4=Alexander A. |last5=Kasinathan|first5=Deepa |last6=Schnelle|first6=Walter |last7=Richter|first7=Asta |last8=Merlini|first8=Marco |last9=Hanfland|first9=Michael |last10=Abakumov|first10=Artem M. |last11=Batuk|first11=Dmitry |last12=Van Tendeloo|first12=Gustaaf |last13=Nakajima|first13=Yoichi |last14=Kolmogorov|first14=Aleksey N. |last15=Dubrovinsky|first15=Leonid |bibcode=2013PhRvL.111o7002G |pmid=24160619 |arxiv=1304.5106}}</ref> Its molecular structure was predicted using computer models.<ref>{{cite news |author=Rachel Coker |title=First Computer-Designed Superconductor Created |url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2013/10/131008132851.htm |accessdate=25 November 2013 |newspaper=ScienceDaily |date=8 October 2013}}</ref>
