{{Infobox storm | name = Sandon tornado | image = | alt = | caption = | formed = 13 November 1976 | active = | dissipated = | lowest pressure = | lowest temperature = | tornadoes = | fujitascale = F3 | tornado duration = | highest winds = | gusts = | maximum snow = | power outages = | total fatalities = 2 fatalities | damages = [[A$]]10.5 million | affected = Sandon / [[Castlemaine, Victoria|Castlemaine]] | location = | current advisories = | enhanced = | notes = }} The '''Sandon tornado''' struck the township of Sandon, [[Victoria, Australia|Victoria]], [[Australia]] on 13 November 1976. The [[tornado]] is likely to have been an F3 on the [[Fujita scale]]. It killed two people when their parked car was picked up and lifted around 9&nbsp;metres off the ground and thrown 100&nbsp;metres into a ditch.<ref>{{cite web |title = EMA Disasters Database |url = http://www.ema.gov.au/ema/emadisasters.nsf/83edbd0553620d8cca256d09001fc8fd/9834ae0250241824ca256d3300057bbb?OpenDocument&Highlight=0,Sandon |publisher = Emergency Management Australia |accessdate = 2008-04-05 }}</ref>
