'''Sven Peek''' is an [[environmentalist]] and activist from [[Durban]], South Africa. He was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 1998, for his efforts on improvement of pollution problems in the region of South Durban.<ref name=goldman-alphabetical>{{cite web |url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/recipients/alphalist |title=Alphabetical list of all recipients |publisher=Goldman Environmental Prize |accessdate=11 January 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101123021216/http://goldmanprize.org/recipients/alphalist |archivedate=23 November 2010 |df= }}</ref><ref name=goldman>{{cite web |url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/154 |title=Africa 1998. Sven "Bobby" Peek. South Africa. Toxic & Nuclear Contamination |publisher=Goldman Environmental Prize |accessdate=11 January 2011}}</ref>

